aVBritish Prime Minister Theresa May "gets frustrated" when people describe her as "robotic | Ben Stansall/AFP via Getty Images Theresa May: \u2018I don\u2019t think I am the least bit robotic\u2019 British PM makes a trip to Lord\u2019s to watch the cricket.\u000a\u000aBritish Prime Minister Theresa May \u201cgets frustrated\u201d when people describe her as \u201crobotic,\u201d she said Friday.\u000a\u000a\u201cI don\u2019t think I am the least bit robotic,\u201d she said in an interview with BBC Radio\u2019s Test Match Special during a break in live coverage of the England vs. West Indies cricket match at the Lord\u2019s ground in London.\u000a\u000aMay, a keen cricket fan, was repeatedly called robotic \u2014 and dubbed the \u201cMaybot\u201d \u2014 during the campaign ahead of June\u2019s snap election, in which her interactions with the public were said to be stilted and awkward.\u000a\u000aThe unflattering nicknames were even used by her fellow Tory MPs. \u201cThere was no sign of the Maybot,\u201d said one MP, speaking on condition of anonymity, after the prime minster addressed Conservative lawmakers following the disastrous election in which she lost her parliamentary majority.
