aVPosted 04 September, 2017\u000a\u000aThe European Commission is seeking to recruit a Director of Croatian nationality, one for its Directorate-General for Justice and Consumers (DG JUST).\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aDirector for Consumers (COM/2017/10374)\u000a\u000aWithin DG JUST, leading a Directorate of some 85 staff responsible for:\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a- Coordinating the formulation, adoption and implementation of consumer policy and legal instruments in accordance with the horizontal priorities of the Commission;\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a- Implementing the consumer programme on safety, education and information, building consumer markets knowledge;\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a- Proposing, implementing and enforcing consumer legislation while fostering relations with the Consumers, Health, Agriculture and Food Executive Agency on consumer aspects.\u000a\u000aThe European Commission applies an active equal opportunities policy aimed at further increasing the share of women in management functions and it particularly encourages applications from women.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a
