aVPhoto: Eduardo Munoz Alvarez/AFP/Getty Images\u000a\u000aNew Jersey governor Chris Christie broke ranks with Donald Trump\u2019s other top allies this morning and refused to defend the candidate for bragging about groping women. He didn\u2019t, however, back down from supporting Trump.\u000a\u000a\u201cThat kind of talk and conversation even in private is just unacceptable,\u201d he said on Boomer & Carton, a sports talk-radio show on WFAN. \u201cI was really disturbed and disappointed by it and embarrassed for him and his family.\u201d\u000a\u000aWhen asked if Trump\u2019s remarks have caused him to waver in his support, Christie said, \u201cThis election is about bigger issues,\u201d and that Trump\u2019s admission to grabbing women may be gross, but \u201cI don\u2019t think it\u2019s the only way you should make a judgment.\u201d
