aVPosted 04 September, 2017\u000a\u000aThe European Commission is seeking to recruit a Director of Croatian nationality, one for its Directorate-General for Employment, Social Affairs and Inclusion (DG EMPL).\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aDirector for Social Affairs (COM/2017/10375)\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aWithin DG EMPL, leading a Directorate of some 95 staff responsible for:\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a- Promoting, monitoring and assessing strategies to strengthen both social protection systems and wider social policies which foster social and labour market inclusion;\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a- Programming and implementing the European Social Fund, the Youth Employment Initiative and the Fund for European Aid to the most deprived;\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a- Contributing to the reform agenda in Germany, Austria, Slovenia, Croatia, Cyprus and Greece through country-specific knowledge and expertise.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000aThe European Commission applies an active equal opportunities policy aimed at further increasing the share of women in management functions and it particularly encourages applications from women.\u000a\u000a\u000a\u000a
