aV\u201cHurricane Irma is of epic proportion, perhaps bigger than we have ever seen. Be safe and get out of its way, if possible. Federal G is ready!\u201d President Donald Trump wrote online Friday morning. | Shawn Thew/Getty Images Trump warns people to stay out of Hurricane Irma's path\u000a\u000aPresident Donald Trump warned Friday that Hurricane Irma, on track to make landfall in southern Florida this weekend, \u201cis of epic proportion,\u201d telling Floridians to heed government warnings and get out of the storm\u2019s path.\u000a\u000a\u201cHurricane Irma is of epic proportion, perhaps bigger than we have ever seen. Be safe and get out of its way, if possible. Federal G is ready!\u201d the president wrote online Friday morning.\u000a\u000aStory Continued Below\u000a\u000aHurricane Irma, which churned through the Atlantic as a Category 5 hurricane before slamming into islands in the Caribbean, made history as one of the most powerful storms ever recorded. It is forecaste to slam into South Florida late Saturday night or early Sunday morning as a Category 4 storm, making its way up the Florida peninsula and then into Georgia and beyond.\u000a\u000aThe president has taken a keen interest in hurricane preparations and recovery, having already dealt with one powerful storm, Harvey, which devastated the Texas coast and triggered historic flooding in Houston. Trump twice visited the Gulf Coast in the wake of Harvey and struck a deal with Democrats this week to offer relief funding to the storm\u2019s victims, as well as fund the government and raise the debt ceiling for three months.\u000a\u000aThe most reliable politics newsletter. Sign up for POLITICO Playbook and get the latest news, every morning \u2014 in your inbox. Email Sign Up By signing up you agree to receive email newsletters or alerts from POLITICO. You can unsubscribe at any time.\u000a\u000aOn Twitter Friday morning, Trump praised the Coast Guard\u2019s life-saving efforts during Harvey but warned that Irma could prove even more damaging.\u000a\u000a\u201cOur incredible U.S. Coast Guard saved more than 15,000 lives last week with Harvey. Irma could be even tougher. We love our Coast Guard!\u201d the president said.
